<h1>CtrlZ jQuery plugin</h1>
<p>With this plugins, you can use ctrl+z and ctrl+y on your textareas, even when 
they are modified by external plugins or javascript routines.</p>

<p>It works with jQuery 1.8.x and upper.</p>

<p>
File jquery.ctrlZ.debug.js is used to debug the undo buffer navigation.
You don't need it !
</p>

<h2>How to install ?</h2>
<p>Upload jquery.crtlZ.js to your server, in any directory. Let's choose /js/, because we are being so silly.</p>
<p>Of course, you need jQuery 1.8 or up for this to work. Because, you know, it is jQuery plugin.</p>
<p>Then, simply link to the js file in your HTML and the activate crtlZ by calling the ctrlZ method :</p>

```
<script src="js/jquery.min.js" language="javascript"></script>
<script src="js/jquery.ctrlZ.js" language="javascript"></script>

<script type="text/javascript">
jQuery(document).ready(function () {

	$("textarea").ctrlZ();
});
</script>

```


